{
  "texts": [
    "The conventional RL algorithms may be inefficient for the MDP with a large state space or continuous action space.",
    "Moreover, the non-linear modeling capabilities of conventional RL algorithms can be limited, leading to performance degradation.",
    "Thanks to their powerful non-linear fitting capabilities, DL can be integrated into RL to further enhance the performance, i.e., DRL [57].",
    "In DRL, DNN can be utilized to deal with the high-dimension data or fit the Q-function and policy function.",
    "For example, the deep Q-network employs DNN to fit the optimal Q-function [206]."
  ]
}